    "It also preserves the overall consistency of the segmentation while avoiding spurious high-mass classifications driven by uncertain predictions.Using these thresholds, we evaluate the model performance at the voxel level on the test simulation.",
    "Table 6 presents the per-class test accuracy, confirming that overall accuracy is not dominated by the abundant non-halo class but reflects consistent performance across all halo mass bins.",
    "For vipr, the test accuracy remains remarkably stable at approximately 97.5% for all halo classes, with a slight drop for the background (85.3%).",
    "In contrast, copra shows a gradual decline in accuracy with increasing halo mass, from 94.3% in the lowest mass bin to 88.0% in the highest.",
    "The background accuracy for copra is similar to that of vipr (85.2%)."
